CLOSURE_REASON: Case Closed Case Noted  The Boston Parks and Recreation Tree maintenance division will only remove the tree and grind the stump that is in the tree pit in regards to the issue that it is causing. Proof would include pictures of the roots growing through the foundation and estimates / bills from a foundation company stating that the roots are growing through the foundation and causing damage. Until then the tree will not be removed. Proof of the damage can be sent to Boston Parks & Recreation Department 1010 Massachusetts Ave Boston  MA 02118 Attn: tree maintenance division. If you have any questions please call the park line at 617-635-7275.  A case will also be made to Public Works to repair the sidewalk.

CLOSURE_REASON: Case Closed. Closed date : 2015-11-20 07:04:30.59 Case Noted For the Boston Parks Department to remove a healthy shade tree we need proof of the roots damaging the pipes. Proof would include pictures and bills from a plumber that show the roots from the City tree growing into the pipes. Until then the tree will not be removed. Proof can be sent to 1010 Massachusetts Ave Boston  MA 02118 3rd floor. Attn: Tree Maintenance Division.  Roots do not break sewage pipes  they will however grow into a sewage pipe if the pipe is old and broken  but trees do not have the ability to break a pipe. Here is the link to the Boston Water and Sewer  sewer lateral replacement program. http://www.bwsc.org/SERVICES/Programs/sewer_lateral.PDF
